<recipe>
<title>
Overnight Crockpot Banana Bread Oatmeal
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 6 hours
TOTAL TIME: 6 hours 10 minutes
COURSE: Breakfast
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: crock pot, oatmeal, overnight, slow cooker
SERVINGS: 8
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="12.0">Milk</ingredient><ingredient amount="1.0 Cup">Banana</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 Teaspoon">Cinnamon</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Teaspoon">Nutmeg</ingredient><ingredient amount="">Sugar</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Grease slow cooker.
In a large bowl, stir together oats, water, milk, banana, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Pour into slow cooker.
Cover, and cook on low for 6-8 hours.
To serve, top (in order) with brown sugar, sliced bananas, and chopped nuts.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>